'''Mirwais Ashraf Khan''' ({{lang-ps|ميرويس اشرف خان}}) (born June 30, 1988) is a right-handed batsman and right-arm [[Seam bowler|fast-medium]] bowler who plays for the [[Afghanistan national cricket team]].
==Career== Ashraf made his [[One Day International]] (ODI) debut against the [[Netherlands national cricket team|Netherlands]] at the [[VRA Cricket Ground]] on 30 August 2009. Ashraf also made his [[first-class cricket]] debut against the same opponents in Afghanistan's debut match in the [[2009–10 ICC Intercontinental Cup|Intercontinental Cup]], where in the Netherlands' second [[Innings#Cricket|innings]] he took four wickets for 24 runs to help set up an historic Afghan win by one wicket.
