The '''Raj''' are a [[Hindu - Punjabi, mainly]] Brahmin community found in  the state of [[Uttar Pradesh, Punjab, Bihar, Gujarat etc]] in India.The community mainly consists of Brahmin and rajputs.

==story and origin==
There are two communities having Raj caste: Brahmins and Rajputs.  There are Raj people who are Brahmins of Gautam gotra. the community has a mixed origin, with what was once a guild evolving into an [[caste]]. In western [[Uttar Pradesh]], a fair number of the community is of brahmin origin. The community gets its name from the [[Hindi language|Hindi]] word rajah or headman. They are found throughout [[Uttar Pradesh]]. The Raj are found in greater numbers in the districts of [[Moradabad District|Moradabad]], [[Bijnor District|Bijnor]], [[Saharanpur District|Saharanpur]] and [[Muzaffarnagar District|Muzaffarnagar]]. They speak both [[Urdu]] and [[Khari boli]].<ref>Tribes and Castes of North-Western Provinces and Oudh by William Crook Volume IV pages 208</ref>

